n as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Stubberffyld was born in 1480, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, Rowland Stubberfeyld, was 60 and her mother, Elienor White, was 59. She had at least 1 daughter with John Martimer Jervas or Gervas. She died in 1515, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1480–1515":"1480–1515","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1488–Female":"1488–Surnud","1480–1522":"1480–1522","1500–1575":"1500–1575","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1422–1500":"1422–1500","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1422":"1422","1488":"1488","1575":"1575","1420":"1420","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1480":"1480","1515":"1515","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dean Hill, Cheshire, England":"Dean Hill, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1480–1515":"1480–1515","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1488–Female":"1488–Kuollut","1480–1522":"1480–1522","1500–1575":"1500–1575","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1422–1500":"1422–1500","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1422":"1422","1488":"1488","1575":"1575","1420":"1420","about 1500":"noin 1500","1480":"1480","1515":"1515","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dean Hill, Cheshire, England":"Dean Hill, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1480–1515":"1